  "prompt": "How do I kill the insects attacking plants naturally?",
  "response": "Here are some natural methods to control insects on plants:\n\n1. Companion planting\n- Plant herbs like basil, mint, or marigolds that repel insects\n- Attract beneficial predatory insects\n\n2. Physical removal\n- Handpick larger insects\n- Use sticky traps\n- Spray plants with strong water stream\n\n3. Homemade sprays\n- Neem oil solution\n- Garlic spray\n- Soap water spray\n- Vinegar and water mixture\n- Pyrethrin spray (made from chrysanthemum flowers)\n\n4. Diatomaceous earth\n- Sprinkle around plants to deter crawling insects\n- Works by dehydrating insects\n\n5. Encourage natural predators\n- Ladybugs\n- Praying mantises\n- Birds\n- Beneficial nematodes\n\n6. Biological controls\n- Introduce beneficial insects like lacewings\n- Use Bacillus thuringiensis (Bt) for caterpillars\n\n7. Cultural practices\n- Keep plants healthy\n- Remove diseased plants\n- Rotate crops\n- Maintain good garden hygiene\n\n8. Create physical barriers\n- Use row covers\n- Mulch around plants\n- Install copper tape for soft-bodied insects\n\nChoose methods based on specific insects and plant types.",
